a way that not today.

01:09:30.910 --> 01:09:34.359
Of course, they're acceptable,
and they're stable.

01:09:34.359 --> 01:09:36.550
And we're going to talk a
lot about the last point.

01:09:36.550 --> 01:09:38.740
They're stable because
they're hard to mine,

01:09:38.740 --> 01:09:42.740
and Bitcoin has that
embedded in it, as well.

01:09:42.740 --> 01:09:45.319
The design of money is
really important, as well.

01:09:45.319 --> 01:09:46.850
You can make it a token--

01:09:46.850 --> 01:09:49.580
a token is like
something physical--

01:09:49.580 --> 01:09:51.649
or account based.

01:09:51.649 --> 01:09:55.440
We're of course now living in
a world of account-based money,

01:09:55.440 --> 01:09:56.780
and it's digital, not physical.

01:09:59.445 --> 01:10:01.070
It can be issued by
the private sector,

01:10:01.070 --> 01:10:04.070
just like banknotes
in the 18th century,

01:10:04.070 --> 01:10:08.040
or private sector like
Bitcoin, or it can be central.

01:10:08.040 --> 01:10:10.920
It can be widely acceptable
or just wholesale.

01:10:10.920 --> 01:10:13.448
There are forms of
wholesale money.

01:10:13.448 --> 01:10:15.240
One of the biggest
forms of wholesale money

01:10:15.240 --> 01:10:17.490
is the central bank's
reserves are only

01:10:17.490 --> 01:10:21.050
available to the
commercial banking system.

